About Genu Berlo

Magnetic Jazz Painting by Genu Berlo

Saatchi Art

Magnetic Jazz

Magnetic Jazz Painting by Genu Berlo 2016

Genu

American - born Romanian

In painting, installation, land art and sculpture Genu reflects on ideas like Grand Design Purpose and Fractality, Magnetic Interaction under Field Awareness, Space-Time-Conscience relations, Inception and Transformation of Amorphous into Sign and vice versa, Embodiment and Substantiality of words into form and matter, Perishable States of Matter and Mind in the context of Life synergy and entropy, Long Life Formulas and Universal Artifacts, Architectural nesting of the Ego. His crossdomain educational backgrounds are of strong influence when it comes to designing structures and spaces embedded with Value Inheritance and Geometric Golden Mean principles, using artistic and architectural means and processes.

With Bachelors in Math and Architecture from the University of Bucharest, Genu (Eugen) Berlo continued his education in Fine Arts at Fashion Institute of Technology of NYC. He worked as an architect for some of the New York City’s most eminent architectural firms, including world’s highly renowned Skidmore, Owings and Merrill (SOM) architectural, planning and engineering company.

@SemneCusute

Untitled Perishable Lightning Rod

Genu - 2016

Ghirdoveni Art Installation

Ludic and Oneiric interpretation of a high raise inhabited building. I imagine here the mix of fear and excitement. Fear of structural soundness against the joy and excitement of inhabiting an architectural skyscraper. Thus, I call this mixed feeling “Untitled Perishable Lightning Rod”, this being one of my artistic studies about Space-Time-Conscience relations and Perishable States of Matter and Mind in the context of Life synergy.

Smoke-Fire Sequence

Ghirdoveni 2015

A study of the very short and volatile manifest nature of smoke and plasma fire sparked by the direct action and awareness of the artist, and sustained by the presence of the universal field Conscience and Earth Ley Lines. The field of mind determining the shape and dynamics of smoke and fire and amplified by the direct placement on a ley line.
